      • incrementRegistrationsTriggerCount

        int incrementRegistrationsTriggerCount()
        Increment and return the number of new user registrations within the current user registrations time block. When no time block is active, a new user registration will begin a new time block, and the registration count returned by this method will begin counting up for each registration. This count will continue to increment for the fixed duration of the time block. In addition to being informational, this provides a means to test for and limit the frequency of new user registrations.
        Returns:
        number of user registrations within current time block
